  "prompt": "How should I improve my vision?",
  "response": "To improve your vision, you can try these methods:\n\n1. Eye exercises\n- Focus shifting\n- Near and far focusing\n- Eye rolling\n\n2. Nutrition\n- Eat foods rich in:\n  - Vitamin A\n  - Vitamin C\n  - Vitamin E\n  - Omega-3 fatty acids\n- Include leafy greens, fish, nuts, and citrus fruits\n\n3. Lifestyle changes\n- Get regular eye check-ups\n- Wear sunglasses to protect from UV rays\n- Maintain proper lighting when reading/working\n- Practice good screen hygiene\n  - Follow 20-20-20 rule (every 20 minutes, look 20 feet away for 20 seconds)\n  - Adjust screen brightness\n  - Use blue light filters\n\n4. Proper eye care\n- Get enough sleep\n- Stay hydrated\n- Avoid smoking\n- Manage underlying health conditions\n\n5. Physical activity\n- Regular exercise improves blood circulation\n- Helps maintain overall eye health\n\n6. Consider supplements\n- Consult an eye doctor about supplements like lutein and zeaxanthin\n\nRemember, if you have persistent vision problems, always consult an eye care professional for personalized advice.",
